---
import Layout from "../../layouts/Layout.astro";
import Article from "../../components/Article.astro";
---

<Layout title="identity">
  <Article
    title="identity"
    section="self"
    updated="archive draft"
  >
    <p>
      identity is the sense of "I"—the structure that holds memory, roles,
      patterns, and continuity together.
    </p>

    <p>
      it appears stable, but is constantly shaped by experience, perception,
      and change. what feels fixed is often a temporary arrangement.
    </p>

    <p>
      because of this, identity is both real and fluid. it organizes life,
      but is never fully complete.
    </p>

    <h2>structure</h2>

    <p>
      identity provides structure. it allows recognition across time: the sense
      that the one who was, is still the one who is now.
    </p>

    <p>
      without this structure, experience would fragment into unrelated moments.
    </p>

    <h2>change</h2>

    <p>
      identity is not fixed. roles shift, beliefs evolve, and new experiences
      reshape what was previously certain.
    </p>

    <p>
      tension arises when identity resists this movement.
    </p>

    <h2>relation to the self</h2>

    <p>
      identity is not the whole self, but one expression of it. it is the visible
      surface of a deeper and more complex process.
    </p>

    <p>
      understanding identity opens the path to questioning it.
    </p>

    <div class="mini-links">
      <a class="link-blue" href="/self">back to self index</a>
      <a class="link-blue" href="/self/intuition">continue to: intuition</a>
      <a class="link-red" href="/self/wanderer">wanderer</a>
    </div>
  </Article>
</Layout>
